{
  "keyword": "CLRLIB",
  "description": "Clear Library (CLRLIB)",
  "parameters": [
    {
      "name": "LIB",
      "description": "Library",
      "help": "Library (LIB)\n\nSpecifies the library to be cleared of all objects for which you have object existence (*OBJEXIST) authority. If you do not have *OBJEXIST authority for an object, that object remains in the library. If QGPL is specified or defaulted via *CURLIB, an inquiry message (CPA2129) is sent to verify that you want to clear the QGPL library.\n\nThis is a required parameter.\n\n指定できる特殊値: *CURLIB",
      "inputType": "text",
      "required": true,
      "attributes": {
        "characterSet": "upper",
        "maxLength": 10
      },
      "positional": 1,
      "basic": true
    },
    {
      "name": "ASPDEV",
      "description": "ASP device",
      "help": "ASP device (ASPDEV)\n\nSpecifies the auxiliary storage pool (ASP) device where storage is allocated for the library to be cleared. If the library to be cleared is not part of the thread's library name space, this parameter must be specified to ensure the correct library is the target of the clear library operation.\n\nNote: If this parameter is specified when *CURLIB is specified for the Library (LIB) parameter, ASPDEV(*) is the only valid value.\n\nNote: To specify a specific auxiliary storage pool (ASP) device name, you must have use (*USE) authority for each ASP device in the ASP group.\n\n指定できる特殊値: *, *CURASPGRP, *SYSBAS",
      "inputType": "text",
      "required": false,
      "defaultValue": "*",
      "attributes": {
        "characterSet": "upper",
        "maxLength": 10
      },
      "basic": true
    }
  ],
  "examples": [
    {
      "code": "CLRLIB LIB(A)"
    },
    {
      "code": "CLRLIB LIB(INVENTORY) ASPDEV(SALES)"
    }
  ],
  "source": {
    "url": "https://www.ibm.com/docs/en/ssw_ibm_i_74/cl/clrlib.htm",
    "version": "IBM i 7.4"
  },
